com.path.android.jobqueue

Enum JobStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<JobStatus>
      • com.path.android.jobqueue.JobStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<JobStatus>

    public enum JobStatus
extends java.lang.Enum<JobStatus>
    Identifies the current status of a job if it is in the queue

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      RUNNING
      Job is being executed by one of the runners.
      UNKNOWN
      Job is not known by job queue.
      WAITING_NOT_READY
      Job is in the queue but cannot run yet.
      WAITING_READY
      Job is in the queue, ready to be run.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • WAITING_NOT_READY

        public static final JobStatus WAITING_NOT_READY
        Job is in the queue but cannot run yet. As of v 1.1, this might be:
        • Job requires network but there is no available network connection
        • Job is delayed. We are waiting for the time to pass

      • WAITING_READY

        public static final JobStatus WAITING_READY
        Job is in the queue, ready to be run. Waiting for an available consumer.

      • RUNNING

        public static final JobStatus RUNNING
        Job is being executed by one of the runners.

      • UNKNOWN

        public static final JobStatus UNKNOWN
        Job is not known by job queue.

        This might be:

        • Invalid ID
        • Job has been completed
        • Job has failed
        • Job has just been added, about to be delivered into a queue
